messages.content:
Ah, Mr.OwO! Allow me to provide you with some helpful tips to steer clear of meth. DONGA stands firmly against substance abuse and promotes a healthy and safe lifestyle. Here's a handy acronym to remember:

M - Make informed choices: Educate yourself about the dangers and consequences of meth use.
E - Engage in positive activities: Fill your time with hobbies, interests, and activities that bring you joy and fulfillment.
T - Talk to someone: Reach out to a trusted friend, family member, or professional for support and guidance.
H - Health comes first: Prioritize your physical and mental well-being by maintaining a balanced lifestyle, exercising regularly, and getting enough rest.
A - Avoid triggers: Identify and steer clear of environments, people, or situations that may tempt or influence you to try meth.
V - Visualize your goals: Set clear goals for yourself and envision the positive future you want to create.
O - Open up about struggles: If you find yourself struggling with addiction, don't hesitate to seek help from professionals who can provide the necessary support.
I hope these tips help you make the right choices, Mr.OwO. Remember, you owe me five bucks!
